'''Shikobuchi Shrine''' (思古渕社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Kuta, Kyoto|ja|久多|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Sakyo Ward|ja|左京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Japan. It is also known as '''Shikobuchi Jinja''' (志古淵神社). Under the {{ill|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, it was classified as a village shrine.
==Deity== * {{ill|Shiko Buchi no Kami|ja|思子淵神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
==History== Shikobuchi Shrine is one of the {{ill|Seven Shikobuchi Shrines|ja|七シコブチ|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The exact date of its establishment is unknown, but records show that it was already enshrined at this location in the first year of {{ill|Tenpuku|ja|天福|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1233) according to the "Kuta Tanoshirabe Chushinjō."
==Festivals and Rituals== * **Archery Initiation (弓はじめ)** - January 3 ** The archery ritual of Kuta was registered as an {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of Kyoto City in 1998. * **Uma Matsuri (午祭り)** - May 5 * **Annual Festival (祭礼)** - Sunday closest to June 19 * **Hanagasa Odori (花笠踊)** - August 24 ** The Kuta Hanagasa Dance was selected as an "Intangible Cultural Property to be Recorded" in 1972 and designated an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property in 1997. * **Tenten (てんてん)** - Sunday closest to September 9
==Sub-Shrines== * **Wakamiya Shrine (若宮社)** - Enshrines {{ill|Emperor Ojin|ja|応神天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Some sources, like "Atago-gun Sonshi," suggest it enshrines a figure named Chūnagon Kanetada, though details about Kanetada are unclear. * **Yama Shrine (山神社)** - Enshrines {{ill|Oyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
==References== * "Atago-gun Sonshi," Kyoto Prefecture Atago District Office, 1911 * "Kuta Hanagasa Odori Survey Report," Geinōshi Kenkyūkai, Kuta Hanagasa Odori Preservation Society, 1974
==See Also== * {{ill|Kappa (folklore)|ja|河童|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
==External Links== * [http://www.kyobunka.or.jp/hanagasa/h-1.html Kuta Hanagasa Dance] (Kyoto City Cultural Property Protection Foundation) {{Atago Faith}}
