==Deity== * {{ill|Shiko Buchi no Kami|ja|思子淵神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiko Buchi no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
==History== Shikobuchi Shrine is one of the {{ill|Seven Shikobuchi Shrines|ja|七シコブチ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seven Shikobuchi Shrines|qq=}}. The exact date of its establishment is unknown, but records show that it was already enshrined at this location in the first year of {{ill|Tenpuku|ja|天福|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpuku|qq=|1=Tenpuku|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1305722}} (1233) according to the "Kuta Tanoshirabe Chushinjō."
==Festivals and Rituals== * **Archery Initiation (弓はじめ)** - January 3 ** The archery ritual of Kuta was registered as an {{ill|Intangible Folk Cultural Property|ja|無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Intangible Folk Cultural Property|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 民俗文化財|1=Folk Cultural Property of Japan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q24895900}} of Kyoto City in 1998. * **Uma Matsuri (午祭り)** - May 5 * **Annual Festival (祭礼)** - Sunday closest to June 19 * **Hanagasa Odori (花笠踊)** - August 24 ** The Kuta Hanagasa Dance was selected as an "Intangible Cultural Property to be Recorded" in 1972 and designated an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property in 1997. * **Tenten (てんてん)** - Sunday closest to September 9
==Sub-Shrines== * **Wakamiya Shrine (若宮社)** - Enshrines [[:en:Emperor Ōjin|Emperor Ojin]]. Some sources, like "Atago-gun Sonshi," suggest it enshrines a figure named Chūnagon Kanetada, though details about Kanetada are unclear. * **Yama Shrine (山神社)** - Enshrines {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|lt=Ōyamatsumi|lt=Oyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオヤマツミ}}.
==References== * "Atago-gun Sonshi," Kyoto Prefecture Atago District Office, 1911 * "Kuta Hanagasa Odori Survey Report," Geinōshi Kenkyūkai, Kuta Hanagasa Odori Preservation Society, 1974
